The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 14 March is 239,676 (27,624.1 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 09 March, there were 6,506 new confirmed cases (749.9 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 02 March, there were 4,100 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 59% (2,406 extra cases).
